cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is about human-object interaction recognition, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a multi-stage, coarse-to-fine architecture, which involves instance localization and interaction recognition networks, indicating a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence, hence cs.AI and cs.LG (Learning) are also likely categories. The paper also mentions cross-stage information propagation, which suggests a potential interest in robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible category. Finally, the paper mentions fine-grained pixel-wise relation segmentation, indicating a potential interest in multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category as well.
